# Dependency Array ðŸ§Š

`useEffect(callback, dependencies)`

- `[]`: Runs ONLY once (Mount).
- `[count]`: Runs on Mount AND when `count` changes.
- `undefined` (No array): Runs on EVERY render (Bad performance).

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  document.title = `Count: ${count}`;
}, [count]);
```

# Cleanup Function ðŸ§¹

If your effect creates a messy subscription (like a timer or event listener), return a function to clean it up.

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setInterval(tick, 1000);

  // Run when component unmounts
  return () => clearInterval(timer);
}, []);
```

# useContext ðŸ“¡

Avoid Prop Drilling.

Instead of passing data down 5 levels of components, use Context to teleport it.

```jsx
const ThemeContext = React.createContext('light');

function App() {
  return (
    <ThemeContext.Provider value="dark">
      <Toolbar />
    </ThemeContext.Provider>
  );
}

function Toolbar() {
  const theme = useContext(ThemeContext);
  return <div>{theme}</div>; // "dark"
}
```

# useRef ðŸ“Œ

Create a persistent variable that persists across renders BUT does **not** trigger a re-render when changed.

Common use: Accessing a DOM element directly.

```jsx
const inputRef = useRef(null);
// ... <input ref={inputRef} />
inputRef.current.focus();
```

# Custom Hooks ðŸ“¦

Extract component logic into reusable functions.

Must start with `use` (e.g., `useFetch`, `useWindowSize`).

```jsx
function useWindowWidth() {
  const [width, setWidth] = useState(window.innerWidth);
  // ... useEffect listener logic
  return width;
}
```

# Fetch Hook ðŸ’»

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

// Custom Hook
function useFetch(url) {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch(url)
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(data => {
        setData(data);
        setLoading(false);
      });
  }, [url]);

  return { data, loading };
}

// Usage
function App() {
  const { data, loading } = useFetch('https://api.example.com/user');

  if (loading) return <p>Loading...</p>;
  return <p>User: {data.name}</p>;
}
FULL_CODE_END -->
